Digram 2 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is correct for white to push at 1. This seemingly common move takes away black's way of living.
\par
\par After black defends with 2, now white plays dansu at 3!
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Now, it is useless for black to play at \b\f1 A\b0\f0  because white would then play at \b\f1 B\b0\f0  and captures all black's stones.
\par }
