Diagram 3 (Variation)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f2\froman\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b9\'d9\'c5\'c1;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj When white \'a1\'e2 is played, if black captures at 1, then white throws-in with 2. If black plays at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white plays at \b\f1 B\lang1033\kerning2\f2\fs20
\par \lang1042\kerning0\b0\f0\fs18 destroying black's eye and black is finished.
\par \pard
\par White captures black easily. This is one of the basic problems.
\par }
