Diagram 4 (Also)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj If black had a liberty at \b\f1 X\b0\f0 , black's group would in fact be is perfectly alive. In response to white 1, black can play at 2 and black's group is safe.
\par \pard
\par If white plays at 3, black answers at 4 and black's group lives. A single liberty can determine whether black is alive or dead.
\par }
